{
  "texts": [
    "Dimensionality reduction techniques serve as a bridge between high-dimensional representations and human visualization.",
    "The goal is to compress embeddings into lower dimensions while preserving the salient structure, e.g., variance, clusters, or manifold geometry, so that latent state behavior can be more easily examined.",
    "In this work, we study both Principal Component Analysis (PCA) and Uniform Manifold Approximation (UMAP) as the primary methods for dimensionality reduction and visualization.PCA is a widely used method for linear dimensionality reduction.",
    "PCA operates by finding a new orthogonal basis that captures directions of maximal variance in the data [9].",
    "By projecting embeddings onto these principal axes, PCA allows one to rank-order components by their explanatory power."
  ]
}